newspaper:
    play sound click
    choice:
        "Today's newspaper is on your doorstep. Yesterday's issue seems to have vanished into thin air for no reason. Oh well there's other broadsheets."
        "[Read todays newspaper] <span class='prompt'>[[-1 ACTION]]</span>":
            play sound spendAction
            set data.game_map.inHouse false
            add_stat actions -1
            set data.newspaper.readToday true
            run transition_black newspaper
            play sound pageturn
            jump newspaper_menu
        "<span class='prompt'>[[BACK]]</span>":
            jump home
    
newspaper_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "<span class='writtenText'>'THE BLUEHILLS GAZZETE'</span>"
        "[Read the front page]":
            jump newspaper_frontPage
        "[Read an opinion column that will in no way damage your mental health]":
            jump newspaper_opinion
        "[Attempt to win fifty pounds by completing the weekly crossword]" if (!= $data.newspaper.crosswordDone true):
            jump newspaper_crossword
        "[Pick a random horoscope and read it and just sort of hope it applies to you]":
            jump newspaper_horoscope
        "[Chortle at todays political cartoon if it's funny, which obviously it won't be]":
            jump newspaper_cartoon
        "[Accidentaly look at the sports page]":
            jump newspaper_sports
        "[Find something better to do than read the newspaper (easy)] <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
            play sound spendAction
            play sound pageturn
            jump goToGameMap

newspaper_frontPage:
    clear_dialog
    play sound pageturn
    if (== $stats.day.value 2):
        "<span class='writtenText'>STRIKERS KILLED!</span>"
        clear_dialog
        "<span class='writtenText'>Reports claim that over one hundred striking workers were killed in the Brennenburgian port of Port Portennsburg after a tense standoff with the military ended in the warehouse turned fortress being shelled.</span>"
        "<span class='writtenText'>Good on the jerries we say. You give these communists an inch, and they'll take it a mile, and then another mile, and then another, all the way to their masters in Musckow!</span>"
        clear_dialog
        "<span class='writtenText'>The Bluehills Gazettes posits to you this question, readers: Do we in Western Europa want to descend into Muskovite barbarism? No! No we do not!</span>"
    if (== $stats.day.value 3):
        "<span class='writtenText'>RAINER ISLE TO BE SOLD TO OCEANIA IN RETURN FOR 'NON-FUNGIBLE PAINTING' LEAKED DOCUMENTS REVEAL!</span>"
        clear_dialog
        "<span class='writtenText'>The Anglian government has agreed to sell the major military port of Rainer Isle, located in the North American Sea, to the foreign bastards in Oceania.</span>"
        "<span class='writtenText'>In return the Anglian treasury will be received a quote 'non-fungible painting', purported by the Chancellor to be worth 'several times as much as the strategic port so deffo wort[sic] it besides Rainer Isle is a volcano so probably it will exploder[sic] soon anyway and kill the bloody Orientals anyway'.</span>"
        clear_dialog
        "<span class='writtenText'>The painting is supposedly of a sheep acting very silly, but we have been unable to confirm specific details at this time.</span>"
    if (== $stats.day.value 4):
        "<span class='writtenText'>MINISTER FOR AGRICULTURE OBLITERATED IN FORTY TRACTOR DEATH PILE UP!</span>"
        clear_dialog
        "<span class='writtenText'>The Department for Agriculture has today released a statement mourning the loss of Lord Henry Arsecunt, Minister for Agriculture. He was killed in a 400 tractor pileup at the Southfolk tractor and sheep show. Over 50 other attendees were killed in the accident, with scenes observers described as akin to 'watching an alligator have hate sex with a shark'.</span>"
        clear_dialog
        "A photograph clearly shows Penny the sheep next to the minister for agriculture. A tractor is hurtling towards them in the background. Penny appears to have spotted it, and is already beginning to dodge roll out of its path. Lord Arsecunt has not, he's focusing too hard on remembering how to smile like a real person."
        clear_dialog
        "<span class='writtenText'>The Prime Minister has yet to respond to this tragedy, as he is currently out of commission, on urgent trade talks in the American archipelago.</span>"
        if (roll newspapere_frontPage_golf_orb orb 40):
            talk orb talk "He's trying to buy back an island."
        else:
            wait 1000
        clear_dialog
        "<span class='writtenText'>It is not currently know who will replace Lord Asscunt, but famed wheat field lover Theresa Ray-Cism is likely to be in the running.</span>"
        clear_dialog
        "<span class='writtenText'>On brighter news from the Tractor show, Penny the Sheep has won her third consecutive 'little bleater of the year' award! Good for her!</span>"
        "<span class='writtenText'>We'll have more updates on the situation as they come out as long as they come before we go to print.</span>"
    jump newspaper_menu

newspaper_opinion:
    clear_dialog
    play sound pageturn
    "<span class='writtenText'>A MODEST PROPOSAL</span>"
    "<span class='writtenText'>~AN OPINION HELD BY LINDA PENELOPIE-GENOCIDE~</span>"
    clear_dialog
    "<span class='writtenText'>Long time readers will well know that I am a proud suffragette, and as such I acknowledge the objective superiority of the male cranium. Indeed, it is this superiority that makes the concern of trans identifying males dominating the world of 'Arbeiter und Wirtschaft: Zweite Auflage' all the more concerning.</span>"
    "<span class='writtenText'>It seems not a day goes by now without some poor woman, who trained for years in the tactics, strategies, tricks, stratagems, ploys, methods and strategies of 'Arbeiter und Wirtschaft: Zweite Auflage', has her trophy stolen away by some sexual deviant. Examples and retellings of this sad story are too numerous to account. For example, a transvestite won bronze in the world championships qualifying round just last year.</span>"
    clear_dialog
    "<span class='writtenText'>This issue, fortunately, shall not harry us for much longer. It is the aim of all of us here at The Bluehills Gazette to help ensure that the transexual is soon morally mandated out of existence, then this debate can finally be laid to rest, and normality and sanity can once again reign, and women can once more take their rightful place, sucking on men's toes. The radical suffragete dream that myself and my friends at SHIT Alliance have long dreamed of.</span>"
    clear_dialog
    "<span class='writtenText'>Furthermore the boat people must be destroyed. Chadwick, Violet, your mother misses you write soon I've changed xx</span>"
    clear_dialog
    if (roll newspaper_opinion_boardgame_nightmare nightmare 20):
        talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>She's right you know.</span>"
        clear_dialog
    else:
        wait 1000
    if (&& (== $data.ghost.clearEyes true) (!= $data.newspaper.readOpinionPiece true)):
        set data.newspaper.readOpinionPieceCumstain true
        choice:
            talk orb talk "Wait, read that again, Ghost."
            "Morally mandated out of existence?":
                talk orb talk "No no. *Really* read it."
                clear_dialog
                "You squint and look a little closer. Ah, you misread it, what Linda actually said was..."
                clear_dialog
                "<span class='writtenText'>'I'd like to see them all shot and bulldozed into ditches like dead poles. It is, morally speaking, the only course of action if we wish to retain some semblance of sanity in this world. I'd do it myself, if not for the prospect of staining my lovely white gloves.'</span>"
                clear_dialog
                "A small cumstain is splattered just above the word <span class='writtenText'>'morally'</span>. It is unclear how this was printed, but it's definitely journalist cum."
    clear_dialog
    if (&& $data.newspaper.readOpinionPiece (> $stats.day.value $data.newspaper.readOpinionPieceOnDay)):
        "It's the same article. The exact same article. Word for word. Letter for letter."
        if $data.newspaper.readOpinionPieceCumstain:
            "It even has the same cumstain hovering over the world <span class='writtenText'>'morally'</span> like a halo."
    set data.newspaper.readOpinionPiece true
    if (== $stats.day.value 2):
        set data.newspaper.readOpinionPieceOnDay 2
    if (== $stats.day.value 3):
        set data.newspaper.readOpinionPieceOnDay 3
    if (== $stats.day.value 4):
        set data.newspaper.readOpinionPieceOnDay 4
    jump newspaper_menu

newspaper_crossword:
    set data.newspaper.crosswordDone true
    clear_dialog
    play sound pageturn
    talk orb talk "A crossword... how exciting. Let's give this a go, there might be some prize money in it for us!"
    clear_dialog

    set data.newspaper.crosswordResponse (text_field "<span class='writtenText'>Two across: Anglian capital city. (6)</span>")
    if (|| (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "lunden") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "Lunden") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "LUNDEN")):
        add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
        play sound write
    else:
        if (roll newspaper_crossword_one_orb orb 20):
            choice:
                talk orb talk "It's <span class='writtenText'>'Lunden'</span>."
                "Oh, silly me. [Correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'Lunden'</span>]":
                    add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
                    play sound write
                    set data.newspaper.crosswordOrbHelped true
                "I trust my gut. [Don't correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'Lunden'</span>]":
                    run skip
        else:
            wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    set data.newspaper.crosswordResponse (text_field "<span class='writtenText'>Three across: Worst ideology. (9)</span>")
    if (|| (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "communism") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "Communism") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "COMMUNISM")):
        add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
        play sound write
    else:
        if (roll newspaper_crossword_two_orb orb 80):
            choice:
                talk orb talk "It's actually <span class='writtenText'>'communism'</span>. The Bluehills Gazette is being funded by the intelligence services."
                "Oh, silly me. [Correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'communism'</span>]":
                    add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
                    play sound write
                    set data.newspaper.crosswordOrbHelped true
                "I trust my gut. [Don't correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'communism'</span>]":
                    run skip
        else:
            wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    set data.newspaper.crosswordResponse (text_field "<span class='writtenText'>Six across: Saint WHO of Anglia. (9)</span>")
    if (|| (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "dawnsight") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "Dawnsight") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "DAWNSIGHT")):
        add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
        play sound write
    else:
        if (roll newspaper_crossword_three_orb orb 40):
            choice:
                talk orb talk "No. It's <span class='writtenText'>'dawnsight'</span>."
                "Oh, silly me. [Correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'dawnsight'</span>]":
                    add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
                    play sound write
                    set data.newspaper.crosswordOrbHelped true
                "I trust my gut. [Don't correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'dawnsight'</span>]":
                    run skip
        else:
            wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    set data.newspaper.crosswordResponse (text_field "<span class='writtenText'>Nine across: Number of angels said to hang above. (8)</span>")
    if (|| (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "fourteen") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "Fourteen") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "FOURTEEN")):
        add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
        play sound write
    else:
        if (roll newspaper_crossword_four_orb orb 60):
            choice:
                talk orb talk "Wrong. It's <span class='writtenText'>'fourteen'</span>."
                "Oh, silly me. [Correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'fourteen'</span>]":
                    add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
                    play sound write
                    set data.newspaper.crosswordOrbHelped true
                "I trust my gut. [Don't correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'fourteen'</span>]":
                    run skip
        else:
            wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    set data.newspaper.crosswordResponse (text_field "<span class='writtenText'>One down: Delicious treat mined from the earth. (4)</span>")
    if (|| (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "lead") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "Lead") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "LEAD")):
        add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
        play sound write
    else:
        if (roll newspaper_crossword_five_orb orb 60):
            talk orb talk "Sigh... it's <span class='writtenText'>'lead'</span>. I don't agree with the puzzles author, but they decided it was lead."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk lovely talk "I mean *obviously*, Orb, what else would it be? Lamprey? Lobster? Lamb? Titter titter."
                "Oh, silly me. [Correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'lead'</span>]":
                    add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
                    play sound write
                    set data.newspaper.crosswordOrbHelped true
                "I trust my gut. [Don't correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'lead'</span>]":
                    run skip
        else:
            wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    set data.newspaper.crosswordResponse (text_field "<span class='writtenText'>Four down: Dirty WHO should be shot for treason? (10)</span>")
    if (|| (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "communists") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "Communists") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "COMMUNISTS")):
        add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
        play sound write
    else:
        if (roll newspaper_crossword_six_orb orb 80):
            choice:
                talk orb talk "It's actually <span class='writtenText'>'communists'</span>. The Bluehills Gazette is being funded by the intelligence services."
                "Oh, silly me. [Correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'communists'</span>]":
                    add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
                    play sound write
                    set data.newspaper.crosswordOrbHelped true
                "I trust my gut. [Don't correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'communists'</span>]":
                    run skip
        else:
            wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    set data.newspaper.crosswordResponse (text_field "<span class='writtenText'>Five down: The WHAT system is the worst form of government (9)</span>")
    if (|| (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "communist") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "Communist") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "COMMUNIST")):
        add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
        play sound write
    else:
        if (roll newspaper_crossword_seven_orb orb 80):
            choice:
                talk orb talk "It's actually <span class='writtenText'>'communist'</span>. The Bluehills Gazette is being funded by the intelligence services."
                "Oh, silly me. [Correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'communist'</span>]":
                    add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
                    play sound write
                    set data.newspaper.crosswordOrbHelped true
                "I trust my gut. [Don't correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'communist'</span>]":
                    run skip
        else:
            wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    set data.newspaper.crosswordResponse (text_field "<span class='writtenText'>Seven down: First country to capitulate during The Great War. (7)</span>")
    if (|| (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "warsawa") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "Warsawa") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "WARSAWA")):
        add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
        play sound write
    else:
        if (roll newspaper_crossword_eight_orb orb 40):
            choice:
                talk orb talk "Everyone knows it's <span class='writtenText'>'Warsawa'</span>, Orb."
                "Oh, silly me. [Correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'Warsawa'</span>]":
                    add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
                    play sound write
                    set data.newspaper.crosswordOrbHelped true
                "I trust my gut. [Don't correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'Warsawa'</span>]":
                    run skip
        else:
            wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    set data.newspaper.crosswordResponse (text_field "<span class='writtenText'>Eight down: Oestradiol leaf smells of this. (4)</span>")
    if (|| (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "mint") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "Mint") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "MINT")):
        add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
        play sound write
    else:
        if (roll newspaper_crossword_nine_orb orb 80):
            choice:
                talk orb talk "I'm surprised you didn't get this one... It's <span class='writtenText'>'mint'</span>, Ghost."
                "Oh, silly me. [Correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'mint'</span>]":
                    add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
                    play sound write
                    set data.newspaper.crosswordOrbHelped true
                "I trust my gut. [Don't correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'mint'</span>]":
                    run skip
        else:
            wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    set data.newspaper.crosswordResponse (text_field "<span class='writtenText'>Ten down: Anglian fighter-bomber aircraft '(SOMEHTING) MK.II', entered service in 1922. (6)</span>")
    if (|| (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "pigeon") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "Pigeon") (== $data.newspaper.crosswordResponse "PIGEON")):
        add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
        play sound write
    else:
        if (roll newspaper_crossword_ten_orb orb 80):
            choice:
                talk orb talk "Wrong, its actually <span class='writtenText'>'Pigeon'</span>."
                "Oh, silly me. [Correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'pigeon'</span>]":
                    add data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 1
                    play sound write
                    set data.newspaper.crosswordOrbHelped true
                "I trust my gut. [Don't correct your answer to <span class='writtenText'>'pigeon'</span>]":
                    run skip
        else:
            wait 1000

    if (== $data.newspaper.crosswordPoints 10):
        set data.newspaper.crosswordCorrect true

    clear_dialog
    if $data.newspaper.crosswordOrbHelped:
        talk orb talk "All done. We can hand it in at the shop and have the nice lady check it over. If it's right, which obviously it will be, because I checked over your responses, we'll get some money."
    else:
        talk orb talk "All done. We can hand it in at the shop and have the nice lady check it over. If it's right, we'll get some money."
    add_item crossword 1
    jump newspaper_menu

newspaper_horoscope:
    play sound pageturn
    clear_dialog
    if (== $stats.day.value 2):
        "<span class='writtenText'>'Today will present you with opportunities. They might be as small as finding a penny, or as big as finding a pound. There's a lot that could happen really.'</span>"
        clear_dialog
        talk orb talk "Getting the impression the person writing these isn't really trying."
    if (== $stats.day.value 3):
        "<span class='writtenText'>'You will smile today. Maybe.'</span>"
        clear_dialog
        choice:
            talk orb talk "Wow."
            "[Smile] \\"Holy shit it's real.\\"":
                talk lovely talk "Gasp!"
            "We'll see about that. [Frown as hard as you can]":
                jump newspaper_menu
    if (== $stats.day.value 4):
        "<span class='writtenText'>'Today is the end. Endzeit cometh.'</span>"
        clear_dialog
        talk poppy talk "It's right, you know? This is the last day of the game. I hope you've done everything you wanted to!"
        clear_dialog
    jump newspaper_menu

newspaper_cartoon:
    play sound pageturn
    clear_dialog
    if (== $stats.day.value 2):
        run transition newspaper_cartoon_one
        choice:
            "Today's cartoon depicts the prime minister with several stink lines emanating from him. The caption just reads <span class='writtenText'>'Smell the'</span>"
            "Smell the...":
                talk lovely talk "Smell the..."
                talk nasty talk "Smell the... Lovely Lady!"
                talk lovely talk "Eep! Keep your nose to yourself you awful pervert!"
                clear_dialog
                if (roll newspaper_cartoon_smell_orb orb 20):
                    talk orb talk "The cartoonist didn't have time to finish this one. Something came up and distracted him, and apparently no one proofread it before putting into today's paper."
                    talk orb talk "The joke he was thinking of wasn't very good, if it makes you feel any less left out."
                else:
                    wait 1000
    if (== $stats.day.value 3):
        run transition newspaper_cartoon_two
        "Today's cartoon depicts a map of Europa. In central Europa there lulls a great, inky octopus wearing a picklehaube. It's tentacles stretch out across the continent, grabbing smaller countries."
        "In Anglia a sheep bites one of the tentacles back. The octopus looks greatly perturbed."
        "<span class='writtenText'>'HANDS TO YOURSELF, FRITZ!'</span>, booms the caption. It's poorly chosen, given that octopuses don't have hands."
        if (roll newspaper_cartoon_octopus_orb orb 40):
            talk orb talk "This is a repeat from well over a decade ago. The cartoonist took a day off for personal reasons."
        else:
            wait 1000
        clear_dialog
        talk nasty talk "Artistically bankrupt tripe... a disgrace. They should have hired *me* to do this shit. There's about a trillion more interesting things those tentacles could be doing, right Lovely Lady?"
        talk lovely talk "Disgusting!"
    if (== $stats.day.value 4):
        run transition newspaper_cartoon_three
        choice:
            "Today's cartoon is just a picture of the newspaper's political cartoonist on his knees, grovelling under the caption <span class='writtenText'>'Lucy! Take me back!'</span>"
            "Hahaha this guy lost his wife. I bet she took the kids LOL.":
                if $data.newspaper.personalReasons:
                    talk orb talk "Well. That's what the day off was about, I suppose."
            "I shall not laugh at this political cartoonist's misfortune. [Laugh anyway]":
                if $data.newspaper.personalReasons:
                    talk orb talk "Well. That's what the day off was about, I suppose."
        clear_dialog
        talk nasty talk "Cackling. This bops. I hope tomorrow's cartoon is as funny as this one."
    run transition newspaper
    jump newspaper_menu

newspaper_sports:
    clear_dialog
    play sound pageturn
    choice:
        "You open the newspaper up to the sports page."
        "Sports!":
            talk lovely talk "Badminton!"
            talk nasty talk "Sweaty athletic women... locker room after the game... yes... must have it... must bully Lovely Lady while she wears her badminton gear... yes..."
            talk orb talk "I've always thought bowling must be fun. I'd quite like to be rolled down the big aisle, I think."
        roll newspaper_sports_sports_orb orb 20 "Sports?":
            success "":
                talk orb talk "Sport refers to any competitive physical activity or game that uses, maintains, or improves physical ability and skills while providing enjoyment to participants and, in some cases, entertainment to spectators. Sports can improve one's physical health. Hundreds of sports exist, from those between single contestants, through to those with hundreds of simultaneous participants, either in teams or competing as individuals. In certain sports such as racing, many contestants may compete, simultaneously or consecutively, with one winner; in others, the contest is between two sides, each attempting to exceed the other. A number of contests may be arranged in a tournament producing a champion. Many sports leagues make an annual champion by arranging games in a regular sports season, followed in some cases by playoffs."
            failure "":
                talk orb talk "Sports... not sure about those... Sorry."
        "Sports.": 
            talk orb talk "Sports."
            talk lovely talk "Sports."
            talk nasty talk "Sports."
    jump newspaper_menu